=1)\n- (c==1 & d==0)\n- (c==0 & d==1 & (a==1 | b==1))\n\nTherefore, out = (c & ~d) | (~c & d & (a | b)) | (~c & ~d & a & b)\nWe could also express as: out = c | (~c & d & (a | b)) | (~c & ~d & a & b)\n\nActually simplifying further:\nOut = (c & ~d) | (~c & (d & (a|b) | (~d & a & b)))\n\nLet's just directly write the logic implementation.",
